────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  EXTREME SCENARIOS — BEST AND WORST PATHS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  UNLUCKIEST ORDER (worst path):
    Deepest drawdown:       $-163,413.98 (-52.6%)
    Lowest balance reached: $+78,306.94
    Final balance:          $+700,330.54

  LUCKIEST ORDER (best path):
    Deepest drawdown:       $-34,133.82 (-27.8%)
    Lowest balance reached: $+88,501.09
    Final balance:          $+700,330.54

  Both paths end at the same place. The only difference is how
  the balance moved along the way.


================================================================================
  BOTTOM LINE
================================================================================

  After 10,000 simulations of 948 trades:

  1. THE STRATEGY IS PROFITABLE.
     Every single simulation ends at $+700,330.54,
     a +600.33% return on the initial $+100,000.00.

  2. DRAWDOWNS VARY BY TRADE ORDER.
     In a typical scenario, the account drops about 27% from its
     peak at some point. In a bad scenario, up to 54%.

